<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Teeseadus s&auml;testab tee suhtes esitatavad n&otilde;uded, tee omaniku ja liikleja &otilde;igused ja kohustused ning vastutuse liiklusohutusn&otilde;uete rikkumise eest, reguleerib teehoiu, tee kasutuse ja kaitse korraldamist ja rahastamist ning inimeste ja keskkonna kaitset liiklusest tulenevate ohtude eest. </eesti>
<inglise>The Roads Act provides the requirements for roads, the rights and obligations of road owners and road users and the liability thereof for violations of traffic safety requirements, and regulates the organisation and financing of road management, road use and road protection and the protection of humans and the environment against hazards arising from traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee </eesti>
<inglise>Roads </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee on maantee, t&auml;nav, jalgtee ja jalgrattatee v&otilde;i muu s&otilde;idukite v&otilde;i jalak&auml;ijate liiklemiseks kasutatav rajatis, mis v&otilde;ib olla riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse v&otilde;i muu juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku omandis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A road is a highway, street, footpath, cycle track or other construction which is used for vehicle or pedestrian traffic and which may be in the ownership of the state, a local government or another legal person or natural person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tee moodustavad: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following are roads: </inglise>
<eesti>1) liiklemiseks kasutatavad j&auml;rgmised rajatised: </eesti>
<inglise>1) the following constructions used for traffic: </inglise>
<eesti>- s&otilde;idutee ning sellega k&uuml;lgnevale alale sisses&otilde;idu ja sealt v&auml;ljas&otilde;idu tee ning k&otilde;nnitee; </eesti>
<inglise>- carriageways, merging and diverging lanes adjacent to carriageways, and pavements; </inglise>
<eesti>- parkla ja puhkekoht; </eesti>
<inglise>- car parks and rest areas; </inglise>
<eesti>- tunnel, sild, truup ja viadukt; </eesti>
<inglise>- tunnels, bridges, culverts and viaducts; </inglise>
<eesti>- teekattega samal tasandil paiknevad trammir&ouml;&ouml;pad; </eesti>
<inglise>- tramway tracks which are at the same grade with the road surface; </inglise>
<eesti>- liikurmasinarada; </eesti>
<inglise>- lanes for non-road vehicles; </inglise>
<eesti>- liikleja kontrollimiseks ja maksustamiseks m&otilde;eldud ala; </eesti>
<inglise>- areas intended for the inspection of road users or in which road users pay charges; </inglise>
<eesti>- &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduki peatuseks etten&auml;htud ala ja ootekoda; </eesti>
<inglise>- areas prescribed for public transport stops and shelters; </inglise>
<eesti>- piirikontrolli- ja tollikontrollirajatis; </eesti>
<inglise>- border control and customs control constructions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) muud rajatised: </eesti>
<inglise>2) other constructions: </inglise>
<eesti>- teepeenar, haljasala ning eraldus- v&otilde;i haljasriba; </eesti>
<inglise>- shoulders, green areas and central reservations or green strips; </inglise>
<eesti>- tee &auml;&auml;rde liikluskahjustuste kaitseks rajatud kaitseehitis ja m&uuml;rat&otilde;ke ning keskkonnakaitserajatis; </eesti>
<inglise>- defence structures for protection against traffic damage and noise barriers and environmental protection constructions located by the side of a road; </inglise>
<eesti>- liikluskorraldusvahend; </eesti>
<inglise>- traffic control devices; </inglise>
<eesti>- teem&auml;rgistus- ja teevalgustusrajatis; </eesti>
<inglise>- road marking constructions and road lighting installations; </inglise>
<eesti>- tee &auml;&auml;res asetsev muu teehoiurajatis. </eesti>
<inglise>- other road management constructions located by the side of a road. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Teemaa </eesti>
<inglise>Road area </inglise>
<eesti>Teemaa on maa, mis &otilde;igusaktidega kehtestatud korras on m&auml;&auml;ratud tee koosseisus olevate rajatiste paigutamiseks ja teehoiu korraldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>A road area is an area which, pursuant to the procedure established by legislation, is designated for the location of constructions within the composition of a road and for the organisation of road management. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikult kasutatav tee ja eratee </eesti>
<inglise>Public roads and private roads </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikult kasutatavad teed on riigimaantee, kohalik maantee ja t&auml;nav. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) National roads, local roads and streets are public roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eratee on rajatis, mida v&otilde;ib kasutada &uuml;ksnes tee omaniku loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A private road is a construction which may be used only with the permission of the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;ikes 8 nimetatud juhtudel v&otilde;ib erateed kasutada omaniku loata. </eesti>
<inglise>Private roads may be used without the permission of the owner in the cases specified in subsection 33 (8) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Jalgtee ja talitee kasutamine ning p&auml;&auml;semine kinnisasjale, millel puudub juurdep&auml;&auml;s avalikult kasutatavalt teelt v&otilde;i kinnisasja eraldi seisvalt osalt, on ette n&auml;htud asja&otilde;igusseaduses (RT I 1993, 39, 590; 1999, 44, 509). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The use of footpaths and winter roads and access to immovables which cannot be accessed from a public road or from a separate part of the immovable is prescribed by the Law of Property Act (RT I 1993, 39, 590; 1999, 44, 509). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tee omaniku n&otilde;usolekul ja tingimustel ning Maanteeameti ja eratee omaniku vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel m&auml;&auml;rab eratee avalikuks kasutamiseks ning nimetab teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutava isiku teede- ja sideminister riigi huvidest l&auml;htudes. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Transport and Communications designates a private road for public use with the consent and on the conditions of the owner of the road and pursuant to a contract entered into by the Road Administration and the owner of the private road and appoints a person responsible for the organisation of road management, on the basis of national interests. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee omaniku n&otilde;usolekul ja tingimustel ning valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ja omaniku vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingu alusel m&auml;&auml;rab eratee avalikuks kasutamiseks ning nimetab teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutava isiku valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu kohaliku omavalitsuse huvidest l&auml;htudes. </eesti>
<inglise>A rural municipality or city government designates a private road for public use with the consent and on the conditions of the owner of the road and pursuant to a contract entered into by the rural municipality or city council and the owner of the private road and appoints a person responsible for the organisation of road management, on the basis of the interests of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingus n&auml;hakse ette eratee kasutamise kord ja t&auml;histus, h&uuml;vitis eratee omanikule ning teehoiukulude kandjad. </eesti>
<inglise>The contract shall prescribe the procedure for use of the private road, marking of the private road, compensation to the owner of the private road and the parties who bear the road management costs. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Tee liigid </eesti>
<inglise>Types of Road </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Maantee </eesti>
<inglise>Highway </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maantee on v&auml;ljaspool linnu, aleveid ja alevikke paiknev rajatis s&otilde;idukite ja jalak&auml;ijate liiklemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A highway is a construction which is located outside a city, town or small town and which is prescribed for vehicle and pedestrian traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigimaantee on riigi omandis olev rajatis, mis on ette n&auml;htud &uuml;ldiseks liiklemiseks asulate vahel ja l&auml;bi asulate. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A national road is a construction which is in state ownership and which is prescribed for general traffic between or through settlements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigimaanteed on: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following are national roads: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&otilde;himaanteed, mis &uuml;hendavad pealinna teiste suurte linnadega, neid omavahel ja t&auml;htsate sadamate, raudtees&otilde;lmede ja piiripunktidega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) main roads which connect the capital with other large cities, large cities with one another, and the capital and large cities with important ports, railway junctions and border checkpoints; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tugimaanteed, mis &uuml;hendavad linnu omavahel ning linnu p&otilde;himaanteedega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) basic roads which connect cities with one another and cities with main roads; </inglise>
<eesti>3) k&otilde;rvalmaanteed, mis &uuml;hendavad linnu alevite ja alevikega, aleveid ja alevikke omavahel v&otilde;i k&uuml;ladega ning neid k&otilde;iki p&otilde;hi- ja tugimaanteedega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) secondary roads which connect cities with towns and small towns, towns and small towns with one another or with villages, and cities, towns, small towns and villages with main roads and basic roads; </inglise>
<eesti>4) rambid ja &uuml;hendusteed, mis on liikluse korraldamiseks ja liiklusvoogude kanaliseerimiseks rajatud eri- ja samatasandiliste maanteede ristumisalale. </eesti>
<inglise>4) slip roads and connecting roads constructed in junction areas of roads which are grade separated or at the same grade for the organisation of traffic and the channelling of traffic flows. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigimaantee liigi kehtestab ning v&otilde;tab maantee riigimaanteede nimekirja ja arvab sellest v&auml;lja teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the types of national road, include roads in the list of national roads and exclude roads therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kohalik maantee on kohaliku omavalitsuse omandis olev kohaliku liikluse korraldamiseks rajatud tee. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A local road is a road which is in the ownership of a local government and which is constructed for the organisation of local traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kohaliku maantee v&otilde;tab kohalike maanteede nimekirja ja arvab sellest v&auml;lja valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A county or city council shall include local roads in the list of local roads and exclude roads therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;nav </eesti>
<inglise>Street </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;nav on linnas, alevis v&otilde;i alevikus paiknev rajatis, mis on ehitatud v&otilde;i kohandatud s&otilde;idukite v&otilde;i jalak&auml;ijate liiklemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>A street is a construction located in a city, town or small town which is constructed or adapted for vehicle or pedestrian traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Jalgtee ja jalgrattatee </eesti>
<inglise>Footpath and cycle track </inglise>
<eesti>Jalgtee ja jalgrattatee on rajatis, mis on ehitatud v&otilde;i kohandatud kas ainult jalak&auml;ijate, nii jalak&auml;ijate kui ka jalgratturite v&otilde;i ainult jalgratturite liiklemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Footpaths and cycle tracks are constructions which are constructed or adapted for pedestrian traffic exclusively, pedestrian and cycle traffic, or cycle traffic exclusively. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Talitee </eesti>
<inglise>Winter road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Talitee on &uuml;le k&uuml;lmunud maa v&otilde;i veekogu rajatav tee, mis on ette n&auml;htud mandri ja saarte v&otilde;i mandri eri kohtade vahel liiklemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A winter road is a road which is constructed over frozen land or a frozen body of water and which is prescribed for traffic between the mainland and islands or between different locations on the mainland. </inglise>
<eesti>Talitee kasutamise aeg on piiratud. </eesti>
<inglise>The period of use of a winter road is restricted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Talitee rajamiseks vajaliku maa v&otilde;i veekogu omanikul on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda tee rajajalt maa v&otilde;i veekogu kasutamise eest tasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner of land or a body of water which is necessary for the construction of a winter road has the right to demand payment of a fee from the constructor of the road for use of the land or the body of water. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Talitee asukoht, tee kasutamise t&auml;htaeg ja kasutamise tingimused ning tee rajamiseks vajaliku maa v&otilde;i veekogu kasutamise eest v&otilde;etava tasu suurus n&auml;hakse ette maa v&otilde;i veekogu omaniku ja talitee rajamisest huvitatud isiku vahel s&otilde;lmitud lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The location of a winter road, the term for and conditions of use of the road and the size of the fee charged for use of the land or body of water necessary for construction of the road are prescribed by a contract entered into by the owner of the land or body of water and the person interested in construction of the winter road. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Maantee klass </eesti>
<inglise>Classes of road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maantee klass m&auml;&auml;ratakse, arvestades liiklussagedust, piirkonna arengu vajadusi ja rahvusvahelist liiklust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The class of a road shall be determined considering traffic volume, the development needs of the region and international traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigimaantee klassi m&auml;&auml;rab teede- ja sideminister ning kohaliku maantee klassi valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>The class of a national road shall be determined by the Minister of Transport and Communications and the class of a local road shall be determined by the rural municipality or city council. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maantee klassid on kiirtee, I klassi maantee, II klassi maantee, III klassi maantee, IV klassi maantee ja V klassi maantee. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The classes of roads are motorways, Class I roads, Class II roads, Class III roads, Class IV roads and Class V roads. </inglise>
<eesti>Maanteed jaotatakse klassideks j&auml;rgmiste tunnuste alusel: </eesti>
<inglise>Roads are divided into classes based on the following features: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kiirtee on sellel lubatud kiirusele vastava kattega maantee mootors&otilde;idukite liiklemiseks, mis ei teeninda vahetult teega piirnevaid alasid. </eesti>
<inglise>1) a motorway is a road for motor vehicle traffic which has an appropriate road surface for the speed permitted on such road and which does not service areas directly bordering thereon. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirteel on kaks eri s&otilde;idusuundades kulgevat v&auml;hemalt kahe s&otilde;idurajaga teed, mis on &uuml;ksteisest eraldatud eraldusribaga v&otilde;i muu rajatisega. </eesti>
<inglise>A motorway has two carriageways with at least two lanes each for the two directions of traffic and the carriageways are separated from each other either by a central reservation or other construction. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirtee ei tohi samal tasandil ristuda teise teega ega raudteega. </eesti>
<inglise>A motorway does not cross at grade with any other road or with a railway. </inglise>
<eesti>Kiirteele s&otilde;idetakse kiirendusraja kaudu ja kiirteelt muud liiki teele aeglustusraja kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>Vehicles join a motorway by an acceleration lane and leave a motorway to other types of roads by a deceleration lane. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee peab vastama kiirtee kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kui eeldatav keskmine liiklussagedus on v&auml;hemalt 8000 autot &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas; </eesti>
<inglise>A road must conform to the requirements established for motorways if the estimated average traffic volume is at least 8000 automobiles per twenty-four hour period; </inglise>
<eesti>2) I klassi maantee on kattega ning m&otilde;lemas liiklussuunas v&auml;hemalt kahe s&otilde;idurajaga tee, mis ristub raudteega v&otilde;i teise teega enamasti kahel tasandil. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a Class I road is a paved road with at least two lanes for the two directions of traffic and which crosses mainly at two grades with railways or other roads. </inglise>
<eesti>Teele s&otilde;idetakse kiirendusraja kaudu ja teelt &auml;ra aeglustusraja kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>Vehicles join a Class I road by an acceleration lane and leave by a deceleration lane. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee peab vastama I klassi maantee kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kui eeldatav keskmine liiklussagedus on v&auml;hemalt 6000 autot &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas; </eesti>
<inglise>A road must conform to the requirements established for Class I roads if the estimated average traffic volume is at least 6000 automobiles per one twenty-four hour period; </inglise>
<eesti>3) II klassi maantee on kattega tee, mis v&otilde;ib teise teega ristuda &uuml;hel tasandil. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a Class II road is a paved road which may cross at grade with other roads. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee peab vastama II klassi maantee kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kui eeldatav keskmine liiklussagedus on v&auml;hemalt 3000 autot &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas; </eesti>
<inglise>A road must conform to the requirements established for Class II roads if the estimated average traffic volume is at least 3000 automobiles per twenty-four hour period; </inglise>
<eesti>4) III klassi maantee on kattega tee, mis v&otilde;ib teise teega ristuda &uuml;hel tasandil. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a Class III road is a paved road which may cross at grade with other roads. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee peab vastama III klassi maantee kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kui eeldatav keskmine liiklussagedus on v&auml;hemalt 1000 autot &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas; </eesti>
<inglise>A road must conform to the requirements established for Class III roads if the estimated average traffic volume is at least 1000 automobiles per twenty-four hour period; </inglise>
<eesti>5) IV klassi maantee on kattega v&otilde;i kruusatee, mis v&otilde;ib teise teega ristuda &uuml;hel tasandil. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a Class IV road is a paved or gravel road which may cross at grade with other roads. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee peab vastama IV klassi maantee kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kui eeldatav keskmine liiklussagedus on v&auml;hemalt 200 autot &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas; </eesti>
<inglise>A road must conform to the requirements established for Class IV roads if the estimated average traffic volume is at least 200 automobiles per twenty-four hour period; </inglise>
<eesti>6) V klassi maantee on kattega v&otilde;i kruusatee. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a Class V road is a paved or gravel road. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee peab vastama V klassi maantee kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele, kui eeldatav keskmine liiklussagedus on kuni 200 autot &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evas. </eesti>
<inglise>A road must conform to the requirements established for Class V roads if the estimated average traffic volume is up to 200 automobiles per twenty-four hour period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tehnilised n&otilde;uded maantee klassile kehtestab koos k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tee projekteerimise normide ja n&otilde;uetega teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The technical requirements for classes of road together with the rules and requirements specified in subsection 19 (2) of this Act for the design of roads shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
