<eesti>Tee suhtes esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Roads </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee seisund </eesti>
<inglise>State of roads </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee seisund peab v&otilde;imaldama ohutult liigelda ning olema keskkonnakaitsen&otilde;uete ja tee klassi kohta kehtestatud tehniliste n&otilde;uete kohane. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The state of a road shall enable safe traffic and shall conform to environmental protection requirements and the technical requirements established for the corresponding class of road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Talitee, ohutusrajatiste, liiklusm&auml;rkide, fooride, piirete, t&auml;hispostide ja teem&auml;rgistuse kohta k&auml;ivad ning muud tee seisundi kohta esitatavad n&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements for winter roads, safety constructions, traffic signs, traffic lights, barriers, roadside marking posts and road markings, and other requirements concerning the state of roads shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tee omanik v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 4 l&otilde;ikes 4 v&otilde;i &sect; 25 l&otilde;ikes 6 nimetatud teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutavaks m&auml;&auml;ratud isik on kohustatud hoidma tee k&auml;esoleva seadusega ja selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktidega s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastavas seisundis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The owner of a road or the person appointed as the person responsible for the organisation of road management specified in subsection 4 (4) or 25 (6) of this Act is required to maintain the road in a state which conforms to the requirements provided for in this Act and legislation established on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of roads </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee omanik on kohustatud tee registreerima asjaomases registris. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The owner of a road is required to register the road in the appropriate register. </inglise>
<eesti>Taliteed registrisse ei kanta. </eesti>
<inglise>Winter roads are not entered in a register. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigimaantee registreeritakse riiklikus maanteeregistris. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) National roads shall be registered in the register of national roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohalik maantee, t&auml;nav, jalgtee ja jalgrattatee ning eratee registreeritakse kohalikus teeregistris. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Local roads, streets, footpaths, cycle tracks and private roads shall be registered in the register of local roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teeregistrite asutamise, pidamise ja likvideerimise ning rahastamise suhtes kohaldatakse andmekogude seadust (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155). </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155) is applied with regard to the establishment, maintenance, liquidation and financing of registers of roads. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee t&auml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Designation of roads </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Euroopa teedev&otilde;rgu registris olev tee peab olema t&auml;histatud E-t&auml;hisega, riiklikus maanteeregistris olev tee riigimaantee t&auml;hisega ning kohalikus teeregistris olev tee kohaliku tee nime v&otilde;i t&auml;hisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Roads included in the European road network register shall be designated with the letter E, roads included in the register of national roads shall be designated with the designation of national roads, and roads included in the register of local roads shall be designated with a name or the designation of local roads. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;nav ja eratee peavad olema t&auml;histatud nimega. </eesti>
<inglise>Streets and private roads shall be designated with a name. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Asustus&uuml;ksusesse sisses&otilde;idu tee ja sealt v&auml;ljas&otilde;idu tee peab tee omanik t&auml;histama suunaviitadega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner of a road leading to or from a settlement unit shall mark the road with signposts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teet&auml;histuss&uuml;steemi ja selle rakendamise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The road designation system and the procedure for the implementation thereof shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;nd </eesti>
<inglise>Road protection zone </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee kaitseks, teehoiu korraldamiseks, liiklusohutuse tagamiseks ning teelt l&auml;htuvate keskkonnakahjulike ja inimesele ohtlike m&otilde;jude v&auml;hendamiseks rajatakse tee &auml;&auml;rde kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;nd. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A protection zone shall be constructed alongside a road in order to protect the road, organise road management, ensure traffic safety and reduce any harmful effects to the environment or humans. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigimaantee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi laius m&otilde;lemal pool s&otilde;iduraja telge ja mitme s&otilde;iduraja korral m&otilde;lemal pool &auml;&auml;rmise s&otilde;iduraja telge on 50 meetrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The width of the protection zone of a national road shall be fifty metres on each side of the axis of a lane or, if the road has several lanes, fifty metres on each side of the outermost lanes. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohaliku maantee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi laius m&otilde;lemal pool s&otilde;iduraja telge ja mitme s&otilde;iduraja korral m&otilde;lemal pool &auml;&auml;rmise s&otilde;iduraja telge on 20 kuni 50 meetrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The width of the protection zone of a local road shall be twenty to fifty metres on each side of the axis of a lane or, if the road has several lanes, twenty to fifty metres on each side of the outermost lane. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eratee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi laius on m&otilde;lemal pool s&otilde;iduraja telge ja mitme s&otilde;iduraja korral m&otilde;lemal pool &auml;&auml;rmise s&otilde;iduraja telge 10 kuni 50 meetrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The width of the protection zone of a private road shall be ten to fifty metres on each side of the axis of a lane or, if the road has several lanes, ten to fifty metres on each side of the outermost lane. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&auml;nava kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi laius on teemaa piirist kuni 10 meetrit; v&ouml;&ouml;ndi laius n&auml;hakse ette detailplaneeringus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The width of the protection zone of a street shall be up to ten metres from the edge of the road area; the width of the zone shall be prescribed by a detailed plan. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoid </eesti>
<inglise>Road Management </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiu m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of road management </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiuna k&auml;sitatakse teet&ouml;&ouml; kavandamist, tee projekteerimist, ehitamist ja remontimist, tee ja teekaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi hooldamist, teekasutuse korraldamist ning tee haldamisega seotud muud tegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>Road management is the planning of road construction, and road design, road construction, road repairs, the maintenance of roads and road protection zones, organisation of road use and other activities related to the administration of roads. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiu kavandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Planning of road management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teehoidu kavandades tuleb j&auml;rgida keskkonnakaitsen&otilde;udeid, piirkonna arengu vajadusi ja eeldatavat liiklussagedust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the planning of road management, environmental protection requirements, the development needs of the region and the estimated traffic volume shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti>L&uuml;hiajaline teehoiukava koostatakse kolmeks aastaks ja seda tuleb igal aastal uuendada. </eesti>
<inglise>A short-term road management plan shall be prepared for three years and is subject to annual review. </inglise>
<eesti>Pikaajalist teehoiukava koostades l&auml;htutakse &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegadest. </eesti>
<inglise>The preparation of a long-term road management plan shall be based on terms provided for in legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teehoiukava peab sisaldama: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A road management plan shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kavandatavate ehitus- ja remondiobjektide nimekirja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a list of planned construction sites and road works; </inglise>
<eesti>2) hooldet&ouml;&ouml;de kulude arvestust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a calculation of road maintenance expenditure; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teehoiukulude eelarvet ning kulude katteks kavandatud tulude arvestust riigieelarve, kohalike eelarvete, laenude, v&auml;lisabi ja muude rahastamisallikate l&otilde;ikes. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a budget for road management expenditure and calculations of revenue planned to cover the expenditure from the state budget, local budgets, loans, foreign aid and other sources of financing. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teehoiukava koostab Teede- ja Sideministeerium Maanteeameti ja kohalike omavalitsuste koostatud teehoiukavasid arvestades. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The road management plan shall be prepared by the Ministry of Transport and Communications taking into consideration the road management plans prepared by the Road Administration and local governments. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiu rahastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Financing of road management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teehoiukava kinnitab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The road management plan shall be approved by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoidu rahastatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse kinnitatud teehoiukava alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Road management is financed on the basis of the road management plan approved by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teehoiu rahastamiseks n&auml;hakse riigieelarves ette kulud &uuml;ldsummas mitte v&auml;hem, kui on kavandatud laekumisi j&auml;rgmistest allikatest: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The total amount of expenditure prescribed by the state budget for the financing of road management shall not be less than the proceeds planned from the following sources: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;tuseaktsiisis k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 45 s&auml;testatud ulatuses ja korras; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to the extent and pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 45 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.99 j&otilde;ust. 25.12.99 - RT I 1999, 93, 831) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 25.12.1999 - RT I 1999, 93, 831) </inglise>
<eesti>2) mootors&otilde;idukiaktsiis; </eesti>
<inglise>2) motor vehicle excise duty; </inglise>
<eesti>3) trahvid teekasutus- ja teekaitsen&otilde;uete rikkumise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>3) fines for violations of road use and road protection requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raha jaotus riigimaanteede hoiuks ning kohalike maanteede ja t&auml;navate hoiuks m&auml;&auml;ratakse igaks eelarveaastaks riigieelarves. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The division of funds for the management of national roads, local roads and streets shall be specified in the state budget for each budgetary year. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 alusel m&auml;&auml;ratud raha jaotuse riigimaanteede ehitus- ja remondiobjektide, hooldet&ouml;&ouml;de ja muude teehoiuks vajalike kulude l&otilde;ikes kinnitab teede- ja sideminister teehoiukava alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The division of funds specified on the basis of subsection (3) of this section between construction sites and road works on national roads, road maintenance and other expenditure necessary for road management shall be approved by the Minister of Transport and Communications on the basis of the road management plan. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalike teede hoiuks riigieelarvest m&auml;&auml;ratud raha jaotuse maakondade vahel kinnitab teede- ja sideministri ettepanekul teehoiukava alusel Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The division between counties of funds specified in the state budget for the management of local roads shall be approved by the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Transport and Communications and on the basis of the road management plan. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee planeerimine, ehitamine ja remontimine </eesti>
<inglise>Road planning, construction and repairs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee rajamiseks etten&auml;htud maa-ala planeeritakse ja avalikkust informeeritakse planeeringu koostamisest planeerimis- ja ehitusseaduse (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380) kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The area prescribed for the construction of a road shall be planned and the public informed of preparation of the plan pursuant to the Planning and Building Act (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tee ehitamise eesm&auml;rk on muuta liiklemine ohutumaks, suurendada tee l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imet ja seega soodustada transiitliiklust, parandada keskkonnaseisundit v&otilde;i soodustada piirkonna arengut. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The objective of road construction is to increase the safety of traffic, increase the capacity of roads and thereby to promote transit traffic, improve the state of the environment and promote regional development. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee ehitamise tulemus on uus tee, tee klassi muutumine, uus ristmik v&otilde;i lisarada. </eesti>
<inglise>The result of road construction is a new road, a change to the class of a road, a new junction or an auxiliary lane. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tee remontimise eesm&auml;rk on k&otilde;rvaldada tee-elementide kulumise ja kahjustuste tagaj&auml;rjed. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The objective of road repairs is to eliminate the effects of the wear and tear of road elements and the effects of damage. </inglise>
<eesti>Remondi tulemus on tee-elementide esialgne tehniline seisund. </eesti>
<inglise>The result of road repairs is the original technical state of road elements. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee klass remondi tulemusena ei muutu. </eesti>
<inglise>Road repairs do not result in a change to the class of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tee-ehitusmaterjalide ja -toodete loetelu, mille puhul n&auml;hakse ette n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamine, nendele tee-ehitusmaterjalidele ja -toodetele esitatavad n&otilde;uded ning n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamise korra toote n&otilde;uetele vastavuse t&otilde;endamise seaduses (RT I 1999, 92, 825) s&auml;testatu alusel kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the list of road building materials and products with regard to which a procedure for conformity assessment is prescribed, the requirements set for these road building materials and products and the procedure for attestation of the conformity to such requirements pursuant to the provisions of the Product Conformity Attestation Act (RT I 1999, 92, 825). </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnisasja sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamine </eesti>
<inglise>Expropriation of immovable </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikult kasutatava tee ehitamise korral kohaldatakse etten&auml;htud sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamise suhtes kinnisasja sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamise seadust (RT I 1995, 30, 380; 59, 1006). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the event of construction of a public road, the Immovables Expropriation Act (RT I 1995, 30, 380; 59, 1006) applies with regard to any prescribed expropriation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Asulate vahel ja l&auml;bi asulate &uuml;ldiseks liiklemiseks etten&auml;htud tee ehitamise korral otsustab kinnisasja sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamise Vabariigi Valitsus ning kohalikuks liiklemiseks etten&auml;htud tee ehitamise korral valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the event of construction of a road prescribed for general traffic between settlements or through settlements, the expropriation of an immovable shall be decided by the Government of the Republic or, in the event of construction of a road prescribed for local traffic, the rural municipality or city council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Teeprojekt </eesti>
<inglise>Road plan </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee ehitamise aluseks on projekt ja eelarve. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Road construction shall be based on a plan and a budget. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudeks teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;deks koostatakse projekt v&otilde;i kulutuste kalkulatsioon. </eesti>
<inglise>For other road management work, a plan or a calculation of expenditure shall be prepared. </inglise>
<eesti>Projekti j&auml;rgi tehtavad teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;d on ette n&auml;htud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tee projekteerimise normide ja n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>Road management work performed according to a road plan is prescribed by the rules and requirements for road design specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Projekti suhtes esitatavad n&otilde;uded, tee projekteerimise normid ja n&otilde;uded ning projekti ekspertiisi tegemise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements for a road plan, rules and requirements for road design and the procedure for performance of an assessment of the plan shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Asulate vahel ja l&auml;bi asulate &uuml;ldiseks liiklemiseks etten&auml;htud tee projekteerimise n&otilde;uded annab Maanteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements for the design of roads prescribed for general traffic between settlements and through settlements shall be established by the Road Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalikuks liiklemiseks etten&auml;htud tee projekteerimise n&otilde;uded annab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The requirements for the design of roads prescribed for local traffic shall be established by rural municipality or city governments. </inglise>
<eesti>Projekteerimisn&otilde;uded esitatakse tee omanikule. </eesti>
<inglise>The design requirements shall be presented to the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teeprojektile tuleb teha ekspertiis. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A road plan shall undergo expert assessment. </inglise>
<eesti>Teeprojekti ekspertiis peab ka selgitama, kuidas teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; m&otilde;jutab keskkonda. </eesti>
<inglise>The expert assessment of a road plan shall also identify the effect of road management work on the environment. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ekspertiisi v&otilde;ib teha isik, kellel on asjakohane tegevusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Expert assessment may be performed by a person who holds an appropriate activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teeprojekti peab kinnitama tee omanik. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A road plan shall be approved by the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Ehitusj&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Construction supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; ehitusj&auml;relevalvet korraldab Maanteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Construction supervision of road management work shall be organised by the Road Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ehitusj&auml;relevalve &uuml;lesanne on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The function of construction supervision is to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kontrollida, kas teeprojekt vastab seadustele ja normidele ning detailplaneeringutele ja projekteerimisn&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) monitor the conformity of a road plan to the law, rules, detailed plans and design requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kontrollida, kas teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;l t&auml;idetakse tee-ehitusloaga kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid ja kas t&ouml;&ouml; tegijal on tegevusluba; </eesti>
<inglise>2) monitor compliance with the requirements established by the road construction permit upon the performance of road management work and to verify whether the person performing the work holds an activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teha ettekirjutusi teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) issue precepts for the elimination of deficiencies in road management work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teatada valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele ning maanteeregistrile v&otilde;i kohalikule teeregistrile tee-ehitusloa ja teekasutusloa v&auml;ljaandmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) notify the rural municipality or city government and the register of roads or the register of local roads of the issue of a road construction permit or a permit for the use of a road; </inglise>
<eesti>5) korraldada ehitisega toimunud avarii p&otilde;hjuste uurimist ja teostada omanikuj&auml;relevalvet tee omanikuga s&otilde;lmitud j&auml;relevalvelepingus etten&auml;htud volituste piires. </eesti>
<inglise>5) organise investigation of the causes of any accidents involving the structure and to exercise owner supervision within the limits of authority prescribed by the supervision contract entered into with the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ehitusj&auml;relevalvet v&otilde;ib teostada tegevusloaga isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Construction supervision may be exercised by a person who holds an activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalveametnikul on j&auml;rgmised &otilde;igused: </eesti>
<inglise>A supervisory official has the following rights: </inglise>
<eesti>1) saada projekti kontrollimiseks vajalikke andmeid, t&ouml;&ouml; kontrollimiseks p&auml;&auml;seda takistamatult teele, teha ehitusettev&otilde;tjale ettekirjutusi, kui ehitis ei ole projektikohane ega vasta ehitusnormidele v&otilde;i on muutunud avarii- v&otilde;i keskkonnaohtlikuks, ja m&auml;&auml;rata t&auml;htaeg puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to receive necessary information to review the plan, have unrestricted access to the road to monitor the work, issue precepts to construction undertakings if the structure does not conform to the plan or construction rules or has become unsafe or environmentally hazardous, and specify a term for the elimination of deficiencies; </inglise>
<eesti>2) n&otilde;uda tee-ehitusloa v&auml;ljaandjalt loa peatamist v&otilde;i t&uuml;histamist, kui on rikutud ehitusloaga kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to demand suspension or revocation of a road construction permit from the issuer thereof if the requirements established thereby are violated; </inglise>
<eesti>3) n&otilde;uda ettev&otilde;tjalt teeprojektis v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tulepingus m&auml;&auml;ratud kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele mittevastavate t&ouml;&ouml;de &uuml;mbertegemist. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to demand an undertaking to redo work which does not conform to the quality requirements specified in a road plan or a contract for services. (4) Supervision costs shall be borne by the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) J&auml;relevalvekulud kannab tee omanik. (5) Ehitusj&auml;relevalve korra, tee-ehitusloa ja teekasutusloa andmise ning teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de dokumenteerimise n&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The procedure for construction supervision, the requirements for the issue of road construction permits and permits for the use of a road, and the requirements for documentation of road management work shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee-ehitusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Road construction permit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee-ehitusloa alusel tehtavad teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;d on ette n&auml;htud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tee projekteerimise normide ja n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Road management work performed on the basis of a road construction permit is prescribed by the rules and requirements for road design specified in subsection 19 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Asulate vahel ja l&auml;bi asulate &uuml;ldiseks liiklemiseks etten&auml;htud tee tee-ehitusloa annab Maanteeamet ning kohalikuks liiklemiseks etten&auml;htud tee tee-ehitusloa valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Road construction permits for roads prescribed for general traffic between settlements and through settlements shall be issued by the Road Administration and road construction permits for roads prescribed for local traffic shall be issued by the rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee-ehitusluba antakse tee omanikule. </eesti>
<inglise>A road construction permit shall be issued to the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&otilde;&otilde;rale maale tee rajamise tee-ehitusluba antakse p&auml;rast servituudi kandmist kinnistusraamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A road construction permit for construction of a road on the land of another shall be issued after entry of the servitude in the land register. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;ks antakse tee-ehitusluba, kui teeprojekt vastab projekteerimisn&otilde;uetele ning ehitusnormidele ja teistele &otilde;igusaktidele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A road construction permit shall be issued for road management work if the road plan conforms to design requirements, construction rules and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tee-ehitusloaga m&auml;&auml;ratakse teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; t&auml;htaeg, j&auml;relevalveametnik ja t&ouml;&ouml; alustamisest teatamise kohustus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A road construction permit shall specify the term of road management work, the supervisory official and the duty to give notification of the commencement of work. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tee-ehitusluba antakse kuu aja jooksul p&auml;rast loataotluse saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A road construction permit shall be issued within one month after receipt of an application for a permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa v&auml;ljaandjal on &otilde;igus tunnistada luba kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The issuer of the permit has the right to revoke the permit if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;d ei ole alustatud tee-ehitusloa v&auml;ljaandmisest arvates &uuml;he aasta jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) work does not commence within one year after issue of the road construction permit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;d j&auml;tkata on ohtlik; </eesti>
<inglise>2) it is dangerous to continue the work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) rikutakse teehoiut&ouml;id reguleerivaid &otilde;igusakte; </eesti>
<inglise>3) legislation regulating road management work is violated; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ei j&auml;rgita teeprojekti v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>4) the road plan is not adhered to or </inglise>
<eesti>5) rikutakse muid tee-ehitusloaga etten&auml;htud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>5) other requirements prescribed by the road construction permit are violated. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tasulise tee ehitamiseks tee-ehitusluba andes tuleb arvestada, et liiklejal peab olema v&otilde;imalik sihtpunkti s&otilde;ita m&ouml;&ouml;da tasuta teed, v&auml;lja arvatud mandrit saarega &uuml;hendava silla &uuml;letamine ja tunneli l&auml;bimine. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Upon the issue of a road construction permit for a toll road, the fact that a road user must be able to reach the required destination by a non-toll road, except when crossing a bridge or passing through a tunnel which connects the mainland with an island, shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasuta tee kasutamine ei tohi p&otilde;hjustada liiklejale liigseid kulutusi ja v&otilde;tta liigselt aega. </eesti>
<inglise>The use of a non-toll road shall not cause a road user excessive costs or take an excessive amount of time. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Tee-ehitusluba ei anta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A road construction permit shall not be granted if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teeprojekt ei ole detailplaneeringu ja projekteerimisn&otilde;uete kohane; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the road plan does not conform to the requirements for the detailed plan or with design requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teeprojekti ei ole koostanud v&otilde;i kontrollinud asjakohase tegevusloaga isik; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the road plan was not prepared or reviewed by a person holding an appropriate activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) projekteeritud ehitis kahjustab asja&otilde;igusseaduse &sect;-des 143-154 s&auml;testatud naabrus&otilde;igusi ja kui naabriga ei ole saavutatud kokkulepet; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the designed structure damages the neighbourhood rights provided for in &sect;&sect; 143-154 of the Law of Property Act and no agreement is reached with the neighbour; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teeprojekt ei vasta tee projekteerimise normidele ja n&otilde;uetele ning teistele &otilde;igusaktidele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the road plan does not conform to the rules and requirements of road design or other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Teekasutusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Permit for use of road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee kasutamiseks annab loa tee-ehitusloa andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A permit for the use of a road shall be issued by the issuer of the road construction permit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teekasutusloa v&otilde;ib anda p&auml;rast tee projektikohast valmimist ja ehitusj&auml;relevalve ettekirjutuste t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A permit for the use of a road may be issued after construction of the road is completed in conformity with the road plan and after construction supervision precepts are complied with. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tee kantakse teeregistrisse p&auml;rast teekasutusloa saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A road shall be entered in a register of roads after a permit is obtained for the use of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ehitatava v&otilde;i remonditava tee v&otilde;ib teekasutusloa alusel v&otilde;tta valminud osade kaupa kasutusele juhul, kui on tagatud liiklusohutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Completed parts of a road under construction or repair may be used on the basis of a permit for the use of a road if traffic safety is ensured. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee likvideerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Liquidation of road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee v&otilde;ib likvideerida, kui seda p&auml;rast uue tee ehitamist v&otilde;i m&otilde;nel muul p&otilde;hjusel enam ei vajata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A road may be liquidated if the road is not needed after the construction of a new road or for any other reason. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee likvideerimise loa annab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>Permission for the liquidation of a road shall be granted by a rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus v&otilde;ib lubada tee likvideerida ilma asjakohase projektita. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A rural municipality or city government may permit the liquidation of a road without an appropriate plan. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Teedokumentide s&auml;ilitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Maintenance of road documents </inglise>
<eesti>Teeprojekti ja muud olulised dokumendid peab s&auml;ilitama tee omanik. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner of a road shall maintain the road plan and other essential documents. </inglise>
<eesti>Teekasutusloa saamisest arvates k&uuml;mne aasta p&auml;rast antakse teedokumendid arhiivi, kus neid s&auml;ilitatakse arhiiviseaduses (RT I 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 16, 271) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The documents shall be transferred to an archives ten years after a permit is obtained for the use of the road and the documents shall be maintained in the archives pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Archives Act (RT I 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 16, 271). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiu korraldajad </eesti>
<inglise>Organisers of road management </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teehoidu korraldab tee omanik Euroopa lepingu (RT II 1995, 22-27, 120), riigihangete seaduse (RT I 2000, 84, 534; 2001, 34, 189) ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse ning nende alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Road management shall be organised by the owner of the road pursuant to the European Agreement (RT II 2000, 22-27, 120), the Public Procurement Act (RT I 2000, 84, 534; 2001, 34, 189), this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maanteeamet korraldab riigi omandis olevatel teedel teehoidu ja on kohustatud looma tingimused ohutuks liiklemiseks nendel teedel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Road Administration shall organise the management of roads in state ownership and is required to create the conditions for safe traffic on such roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus korraldab kohaliku omavalitsuse omandis olevatel teedel teehoidu ja on kohustatud looma tingimused ohutuks liiklemiseks nendel teedel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Rural municipality and city governments shall organise the management of roads in the ownership of local governments and are required to create the conditions for safe traffic on such roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Eratee omanik korraldab tema omandis oleval teel teehoidu ja on kohustatud looma tingimused ohutuks liiklemiseks tema teel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Owners of private roads shall organise the management of roads in the ownership thereof and are required to create the conditions for safe traffic on such roads. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Talitee rajaja korraldab teehoidu taliteel ja on kohustatud looma tingimused ohutuks liiklemiseks tema rajatud teel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Constructors of winter roads shall organise the management of winter roads and are required to create the conditions for safe traffic on roads constructed thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ajal tagab liiklusohutuse teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; tegija. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Traffic safety during road management work shall be ensured by the performer of the road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiu korraldamise eest vastutava isiku m&auml;&auml;ravad tee omanik ja teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegija lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>The person responsible for the organisation of road management shall be appointed by contract by the owner of the road and the performer of the road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Linnas, alevis ja alevikus on teega k&uuml;lgneva territooriumi kasutaja kohustatud tegema heakorrat&ouml;id s&otilde;idutee ja vastava territooriumi vahel oleval k&otilde;nniteel. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) In a city, town or small town, the user of a territory adjacent to a road is required to maintain the pavement between the carriageway and the corresponding territory. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikult kasutatavate teede ehitamiseks, remontimiseks ja hooldamiseks, nimetatud teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalveks, teede projekteerimiseks ning projekti ekspertiisi tegemiseks on n&otilde;utav tegevusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence is required for the construction, repairs and maintenance of public roads, construction supervision over the specified road management work, road design and assessment of plans. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba antakse f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule, kes on t&auml;itnud n&otilde;uded vastava teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licences shall be granted to natural and legal persons who comply with the requirements for performance of the corresponding road management works. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba on vajalik j&auml;rgmisteks teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;deks: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An activity licence is necessary for the following road management works: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teede projekteerimine, v&auml;lja arvatud tunnelid, sillad ja viaduktid (edaspidi sillad); </eesti>
<inglise>1) road design, except tunnels, bridges and viaducts (hereinafter bridges); </inglise>
<eesti>2) sildade projekteerimine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) design of bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teeprojektide ekspertiis, v&auml;lja arvatud sillaprojektid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) assessment of road plans, except plans of bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>4) sillaprojektide ekspertiis; </eesti>
<inglise>4) assessment of plans of bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>5) teede ehitamine, remontimine ja hooldamine, v&auml;lja arvatud sildade ehitamine ja remontimine; </eesti>
<inglise>5) construction, repairs and maintenance of roads, except construction and repairs of bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>6) sildade ehitamine ja remontimine; </eesti>
<inglise>6) construction and repairs of bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>7) teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalve. </eesti>
<inglise>7) construction supervision over road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juriidiline isik v&otilde;ib taotleda tegevusluba k&otilde;ikide k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Legal persons may apply for activity licences for the performance all road management works specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik v&otilde;ib taotleda tegevusluba teede projekteerimiseks, sildade projekteerimiseks, teeprojektide ekspertiisiks ja sillaprojektide ekspertiisiks ning teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalveks. </eesti>
<inglise>Natural persons may apply for activity licences for road design, design of bridges, assessment of road plans and assessment of plans of bridges and for construction supervision over road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlejale esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for applicants for activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teede projekteerimiseks, sildade projekteerimiseks, teeprojektide ekspertiisiks ja sillaprojektide ekspertiisiks ning teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalveks tegevusluba taotleva juriidilise isiku teenistuses peab igal tegevusluba n&otilde;udval tegevusalal olema v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks p&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;tav teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; kvaliteedi eest vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;taja (edaspidi vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;taja), kellel on vastav f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku tegevusluba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) At least one employee in a principal job who is responsible for the quality of road management work (hereinafter responsible employee) per each area of activity which requires an activity licence, provided that employee holds the relevant activity licence of a natural person, must be employed by a legal person which applies for an activity licence for road design, design of bridges, assessment of road plans and assessment of plans of bridges and for construction supervision over road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teede ehitamiseks, remontimiseks ja hooldamiseks ning sildade ehitamiseks ja remontimiseks tegevusluba taotleva juriidilise isiku teenistuses peab igal tegevusluba n&otilde;udval tegevusalal olema v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes vastab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 3 ja 4 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At least one responsible employee per each area of activity which requires an activity licence, provided that the employee complies with the requirements provided for in subsections (3) and (4) of this section, must be employed by a legal person which applies for an activity licence for the construction, repairs and maintenance of roads and for the construction and repairs of bridges. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusluba taotleval f&uuml;&uuml;silisel isikul ja juriidilise isiku teenistuses oleval vastutaval t&ouml;&ouml;tajal peab olema vastav akadeemiline v&otilde;i rakenduslik erialane k&otilde;rgharidus ning erialane t&ouml;&ouml;kogemus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Natural persons and responsible employees employed by a legal person who apply for activity licences must have completed a relevant academic or applied higher education and have professional experience. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Erialaseks t&ouml;&ouml;kogemuseks loetakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The following are deemed to be professional experience: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teede v&otilde;i sildade projekteerimisel ning tee- v&otilde;i sillaprojektide ekspertiisi tegemisel v&auml;hemalt kolmeaastast t&ouml;&ouml;tamist vastavalt teede v&otilde;i sildade projekteerijana v&otilde;i vastava teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; juhina; </eesti>
<inglise>1) at least three years of employment as a designer of roads or bridges or as a person responsible for a corresponding road management work respectively, upon design of roads or bridges and assessment of plans of roads or bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teede ehitamisel, remontimisel ja hooldamisel ning sildade ehitamisel ja remontimisel v&auml;hemalt kolmeaastast t&ouml;&ouml;tamist vastava teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; juhina; </eesti>
<inglise>2) at least three years of employment as a person responsible for a corresponding road management work, upon construction, repairs and maintenance of roads and construction and repairs of bridges; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalve teostamisel v&auml;hemalt kolmeaastast t&ouml;&ouml;tamist teede v&otilde;i sildade projekteerijana, teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalve insenerina v&otilde;i teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; juhina. </eesti>
<inglise>3) at least three years of employment as a designer of roads or bridges, construction engineer supervising road management work or as a person responsible for road management work upon exercise of construction supervision over road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalve tegevusluba taotlev f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik peab lisaks k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele olema l&auml;binud teede- ja sideministri tunnustatud asutuses teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de ehitusj&auml;relevalve koolituskursuse ja sooritanud kursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A natural person who applies for an activity licence for construction supervision over road management work must, in addition to the requirements provided for in this section, have undergone a training course for construction supervision over road management work in an agency recognised by the Minister of Transport and Communications and have passed the written final exam of the course. </inglise>
<eesti>Koolituskursuse peab tegevusloa omanik l&auml;bima iga kolme aasta tagant. </eesti>
<inglise>A holder of the activity licence shall undergo the training course once every three years. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teede- ja sideminister kinnitab koolituskursuse &otilde;ppekava. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall approve the curriculum of the training course. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Erandkorras v&otilde;ib teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegevusluba taotleda v&otilde;i olla vastutavaks t&ouml;&ouml;tajaks tee-ehitusalase keskeriharidusega isik, kelle senine t&ouml;&ouml;alane tegevus, t&auml;iendus&otilde;pe ning t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja ameti- v&otilde;i erialaliitude soovitused tunnistavad tema p&auml;devust vastaval tegevusalal tegutsemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) As an exception, a person with vocational secondary education in road construction whose previous professional activities, in-service training and the recommendations of employers and occupational and professional associations prove his or her competence to operate in the corresponding area of activity may apply for an activity licence for the performance of road management work or be a responsible employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) V&auml;lisriigi kodaniku ja ettev&otilde;tja suhtes kehtivad teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegevusloa taotlemise korral samad n&otilde;uded, mis Eesti Vabariigi kodaniku ja ettev&otilde;tja suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Upon application for an activity licence for the performance of road management work, the same requirements which apply to the citizens and undertakings of the Republic of Estonia apply to citizens and undertakings of foreign states. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25 (3). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25 (3). </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa saamiseks peab f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik esitama Maanteeametile taotluse koos dokumentide koopiatega, mis t&otilde;endavad vastava teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; tegemise oskusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to receive an activity licence, a natural person shall submit to the Road Administration an application together with copies of documents which certify his or her skills to perform the corresponding road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa saamiseks peab juriidiline isik esitama Maanteeametile taotluse, millele on lisatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to receive an activity licence, a legal person shall submit to the Road Administration an application together with: </inglise>
<eesti>1) andmed tema kasutuses oleva vastava teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks vajaliku tehnilise varustuse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) information concerning the technical equipment in the use thereof which is necessary for the performance of the corresponding road management work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud v&auml;ljav&otilde;te asutamisotsusest, -lepingust, &uuml;hingulepingust v&otilde;i p&otilde;hikirjast tegevusvaldkondade kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a notarised transcript of the foundation resolution, memorandum of association, partnership agreement or articles of association with regard to areas of activity; </inglise>
<eesti>3) p&otilde;hikohaga t&ouml;&ouml;tavate vastutavate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate nimekiri, kuhu on m&auml;rgitud nende erialased oskused ja erialased t&ouml;&ouml;kogemused; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a list which sets out the responsible employees in a principal job and sincludes their professional skills and professional experience; </inglise>
<eesti>4) Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuse puudumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a statement from the local Tax Board Office certifying the absence of tax arrears. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25 (4). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25 (4). </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa v&auml;ljaandmine, pikendamine ja muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Issue, extension and amendment of activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegevuslubasid annab v&auml;lja Maanteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Road Administration shall issue activity licences for road management work. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa v&auml;ljaandmiseks hindab Maanteeamet tegevusloa taotleja vastavust k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 25 (2) s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to issue an activity licence, the Road Administration shall assess the conformity of the applicant for the activity licence to the requirements provided for in &sect; 25 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusluba antakse kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Activity licences shall be issued for three years. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivusajal on Maanteeametil &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda tegevusloa omanikult vastutavate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate nimekirja. </eesti>
<inglise>During the period of validity of the activity licence, the Road Administration has the right to request the list of responsible employees from the holder of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloale m&auml;rgitakse j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An activity licence shall set out the following information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegevusloa omaniku nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the holder of the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lubatud tegevusalad; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the permitted areas of activity; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tegevusloa number; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the number of the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tegevusloa v&auml;ljaandmise kuup&auml;ev ja kehtivusaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the date of issue and period of validity of the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tegevusloa andja nimetus ja pitser; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the name and seal of the issuer of the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tegevusloale alla kirjutava isiku ametinimetus, nimi ja allkiri. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the official title, name and signature of the person who signs the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa taotleja tasub loa saamise eest riigil&otilde;ivu vastavalt riigil&otilde;ivuseaduses (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; 2000, 5, 32; 10, 58; 19, 117; 26, 150; 29, 168 ja 169; 39, 237; 49, 300; 54, 346 ja 349; 55, 365; 57, 372 ja 373; 59, 379; 60, &otilde;iend; 78, 498; 84, 534; 92, 597 ja 598; 95, 607 ja 611; 2001, 2, 2; 3, 4; 16, 69 ja 72; 27, 151; 31, 171; 34, 188 ja 189; 36, 201) s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A state fee is charged for the issue of a licence from the applicant for the activity licence pursuant to the provisions of the State Fees Act (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; 2000, 5, 32; 10, 58; 19, 117; 26, 150; 29, 168 and 169; 39, 237; 49, 300; 54, 346 and 349; 55, 365; 57, 372 and 373; 59, 379; 60, correction notice; 78, 498; 84, 534; 92, 597 and 598; 95, 607 and 611; 2001, 2, 2; 3, 4; 16, 69 and 72; 27, 151; 31, 171; 34, 188 and 189; 36, 201). </inglise>
<eesti>Maksekorralduse koopia esitatakse tegevusloa k&auml;ttesaamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of the payment order shall be presented upon receipt of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusloa kehtivusaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel pikendatakse tegevusloa omaniku taotlusel tegevusluba kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon expiry of the term of an activity licence, the activity licence shall be extended for three years at the request of the holder of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tegevusloa pikendamise korral kehtivad tegevusloa v&auml;ljaandmiseks s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Upon extension of an activity licence, the requirements provided for issue of activity licences apply. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tegevusloale kantud andmete muutumise korral on tegevusloa omanik kohustatud taotlema tegevusloa muutmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Upon any amendments to the data entered on an activity licence, the holder of the activity licence is required to apply for amendment of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tegevusloa omaniku taotluse alusel muudetakse loale m&auml;rgitud tegevusala v&otilde;i muid andmeid, ei muutu tegevusloa kehtivusaeg ega v&otilde;eta riigil&otilde;ivu. </eesti>
<inglise>If, on the basis of an application of the holder of the activity licence, an area of activity or other data set out on the activity licence are amended, the period of validity of the activity licence does not change and the state fee is not charged. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Otsuse tegevusloa andmise, pikendamise, muutmise v&otilde;i vastava toimingu tegemisest keeldumise kohta teeb Maanteeamet hiljemalt 30 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi n&otilde;utavate dokumentide saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The Road Administration shall decide on issue, extension or amendment of an activity licence or on refusal to perform any of the corresponding acts not later than within thirty days after the receipt of all the required documents. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlejat teavitatakse seitsme p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast sellekohase otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmist. </eesti>
<inglise>The applicant for the activity licence shall be informed within seven days after the decision to this effect is made. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25 (5). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25 (5). </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa peatamine ja kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension and revocation of activity licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa v&otilde;ib peatada, kui tegevusloa omanik: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An activity licence may be suspended if the owner of the activity licence: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on rikkunud teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de suhtes kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) violates requirements established with regard to road management work; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on esitanud tegevusloa taotlemise v&otilde;i pikendamise korral valeandmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) has submitted false information upon application for or extension of the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei ole etten&auml;htud ajaks v&otilde;i ulatuses t&auml;itnud ehitusj&auml;relevalve ettekirjutusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) does not comply with the construction supervision precepts by the prescribed date or to the prescribed extent; </inglise>
<eesti>4) on juriidiline isik, kelle teenistuses ei ole n&otilde;uetekohase p&auml;devusega vastutavat t&ouml;&ouml;tajat; </eesti>
<inglise>4) is a legal person who does not employ responsible employees with the required competence; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ei ole tegevusloale kantavate andmete muutumisel teinud tegevusloa muutmise taotlust; </eesti>
<inglise>5) does not apply for amendment of the activity licence upon any amendments to the data on the activity licence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ei ole tasunud riigil&otilde;ivu 10 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast talle teatavaks tehtud otsust tegevusloa v&auml;ljastamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>6) does not pay the state fee within ten days after he or she is informed of a decision on issue of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maanteeamet v&otilde;ib anda tegevusloa omanikule t&auml;htaja tegevusloa peatamise tinginud puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Road Administration may grant a term for the holder of an activity licence for the elimination of deficiencies which caused the suspension of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa kehtivusaeg ei pikene tegevusloa peatamise aja v&otilde;rra. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The period during which an activity licence is suspended does not extend the period of validity of the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusluba tunnistatakse kehtetuks, kui tegevusloa omanik ei ole talle teatatud t&auml;htaja jooksul puudusi k&otilde;rvaldanud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An activity licence shall be revoked if the holder of the activity licence does not eliminate the deficiencies during the period of which he or she is informed. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tegevusloa taotluse menetlemise korra, tegevusloa vormi ning taotluste vormin&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the procedure for the review of applications for activity licences for the performance of road management work, the form of the activity licences and the formal requirements for the applications. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25 (6). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25 (6). </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidluste lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of disputes </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i omanik ei ole n&otilde;us Maanteeameti otsusega tegevusloa v&auml;ljaandmisest keeldumise, tegevusloa peatamise v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamise kohta, v&otilde;ib ta esitada kirjaliku kaebuse teede- ja sideministrile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an applicant or holder of an activity licence does not agree with a decision of the Road Administration on refusal to issue an activity licence, suspension or revocation of an activity licence, he or she may file a written complaint with the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaebus vaadatakse l&auml;bi 10 p&auml;eva jooksul ja kaebuse esitajale teatatakse l&auml;bivaatamise tulemusest t&auml;htkirjaga seitsme p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A complaint shall be reviewed within ten days and the complainant shall be informed of the results of the review by registered mail within seven days after the date on which the decision is made. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kaebuse lahendamine v&otilde;tab rohkem aega, v&otilde;ib teede- ja sideminister otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmise t&auml;htaega pikendada kuni 30 p&auml;eva v&otilde;rra, teatades sellest kaebuse esitajale kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>If the settlement of the complaint requires more time, the Minister of Transport and Communications may extend the term for making the decision by up to thirty days and shall notify the complainant thereof in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasuline tee </eesti>
<inglise>Toll road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tasulise tee v&otilde;ib rajada &uuml;ksnes uusehitisena. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A toll road may only be constructed as a new structure. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasulise tee hoiu kulud kannab ja tee kasutamise tasu kehtestab tee omanik. </eesti>
<inglise>The costs of managing a toll road shall be borne and the fee for use of the road shall be established by the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tee-ehitusloa andja v&otilde;ib tasulise tee omanikule kehtestada tee-ehitus- ja teekasutusn&otilde;uded, tee tasulisena kasutamise t&auml;htaja ning teevaidluste lahendamise korra. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The issuer of a road construction licence may establish road construction requirements and road use requirements on the owner of a toll road, a term for use of the road as a toll road and the procedure for settlement of road disputes. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Teel paiknev teev&auml;line rajatis </eesti>
<inglise>Non-road construction located on road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teel paikneva melioratsiooni- ja h&uuml;drotehnilise ning muu rajatise hoidu korraldab selle omanik tee omaniku n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The management of a soil amelioration construction, hydrotechnical construction or other construction shall be organised by the owner of the construction with the consent of the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teed &uuml;letavat viadukti hoiab korras selle omanik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A viaduct passing over a road shall be maintained by the owner of the viaduct. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee&uuml;letuskoht </eesti>
<inglise>Level crossing </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudtee&uuml;letuskoht on tee ja raudtee samatasandilise ristumise ala. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A level crossing is an area where a road and a railway cross at grade. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudtee&uuml;letuskohal teeb ristumiskoha hoiut&ouml;id ja on kohustatud looma tingimused ohutuks liiklemiseks tee omanik ja raudtee omanik vastavalt neile kuuluva kinnisasja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Road management work at a level crossing shall be performed and conditions for safe traffic shall be created by the owner of the road and the owner of the railway to the extent of the immovables in their ownership. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tee ja raudtee kattuvas kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis teevad tee omanik ja raudtee omanik hoiut&ouml;id omavahelise kokkuleppe alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Road management work in overlapping protection zones of a road and a railway shall be performed by the owner of the road and the owner of the railway on the basis of mutual agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikult kasutatava tee maakasutus </eesti>
<inglise>Land use of public road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikult kasutatava tee maakasutuse sihtotstarve on transpordimaa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The intended land use of public roads is land designated for transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avalikult kasutatava tee seisundist v&otilde;i teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;dest tingitud ajutiseks &uuml;mbers&otilde;iduks s&otilde;lmib tee omanik lepingu kinnistu omanikuga, kelle maal &uuml;mbers&otilde;iduks kasutatav tee asub. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to enable a temporary detour due to the state of a public road or due to road management work, the owner of the road shall enter into a contract with the owner of the registered immovable on whose land the road used for the detour is located. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingut ei pea s&otilde;lmima avarii ja loodus&otilde;nnetuse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>A contract need not be entered into in the event of an accident or natural disaster. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalikult kasutatava tee omanikul on &otilde;igus anda teemaad maakasutust reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt kasutada teisele isikule ilma hoonestus&otilde;iguseta tingimusel, et see ei raskenda teehoidu ega halvenda liiklusolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The owner of a public road has the right to allow other persons to use the road area pursuant to legislation regulating land use and without constituting a right of superficies on the condition that such use does not interfere with road management or worsen traffic conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teealuses maap&otilde;ue osas tehtavate kaevandamist&ouml;&ouml;de suhtes, v&auml;lja arvatud allmaaehitiste rajamine, ei kohaldata maap&otilde;ueseadust (RT I 1994, 86/87, 1488; 1995, 75, 1321; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 52, 833; 86, 1461; 93, 1562; 1998, 64/65, 1005; 71, 1201; 1999, 10, 155; 54, 583; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 102, 670; 2001, 24, 133). </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Earth's Crust Act (RT I 1994, 86/87, 1488; 1995, 75, 1321; 1996, 49, 953; 1997, 52, 833; 86, 1461; 93, 1562; 1998, 64/65, 1005; 71, 1201; 1999, 10, 155; 54, 583; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 102, 670; 2001, 24, 133) shall not be implemented with regard to extraction work in the earth's crust under roads, except with regard to the construction of underground structures. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml; tehnoloogia </eesti>
<inglise>Technology of road management work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee ehitamise ja remontimise ning muude teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tehnoloogia peab vastama liiklusohutus- ja keskkonnakaitse- ning tee seisundi suhtes esitatavatele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Technology used in road construction, road repairs and other road management work shall conform to the requirements for traffic safety, environmental protection and the state of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teehoiut&ouml;&ouml;de tehnoloogian&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements for road management work shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Teave tee seisundi ja kasutuskorralduse kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Information on state of road and organisation of use </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigimaanteede seisundi ning nende kasutamise ja kaitse p&otilde;hin&otilde;uete kohta annab teavet Maanteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Information on the state of national roads and general requirements for the use and protection thereof shall be provided by the Road Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>Operatiivinfot riigimaanteede liiklusolude kohta annab Maanteeamet &uuml;leriigilise levikuga raadio kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>Immediate information concerning traffic conditions on national roads shall be provided by the Road Administration on national radio. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maanteeamet peab &uuml;leriigilise levikuga raadio kaudu teatama riigimaantee liikluskorralduse olulisest muudatusest ja selle kehtimisajast v&auml;hemalt 24 tundi ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Road Administration shall give notification of any significant changes in traffic control on a national road and of the period during which such change is in force on national radio at least twenty-four hours in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikult kasutatava tee omanik peab liikluskorralduse muudatusest teatama viisil, mis v&otilde;imaldab teavet saada sellel liiklejal, kes seda vajab. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner of a public road shall give notification of any changes in traffic control in such a manner that the information reaches the road users whom it may concern. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tugeva lumetuisu ja kiilasj&auml;&auml; tekkimise korral ning muul liikluskorraldust v&otilde;i liiklusohutust oluliselt m&otilde;jutaval juhul on Maanteeamet kohustatud &uuml;leriigilise levikuga raadio kaudu viivitamata teatama riigimaantee olukorrast ja andma operatiivinfot loodus- v&otilde;i liiklus&otilde;nnetusest p&otilde;hjustatud liikluskorralduse muudatustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the event of a heavy snowstorm or black ice and in other cases which significantly affect traffic control or traffic safety, the Road Administration is required to give immediate notification on national radio of the state of national roads and to provide immediate information on any changes in traffic control caused by natural disasters or traffic accidents. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) J&auml;relep&auml;rimise korral peab tee omanik andma teavet tee seisundi ja kasutuskorralduse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The owner of a road shall provide information on the state of the road and on the organisation of use thereof if a corresponding inquiry is made. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Tee kasutamine ja kaitsmine </eesti>
<inglise>Road Use and Protection </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee kasutajale esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for road users </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teed ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndit kahjustada ja risustada on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) It is prohibited to damage and pollute roads or road protection zones. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee omanik ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi omanik v&otilde;ivad n&otilde;uda tee v&otilde;i tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi kahjustajalt v&otilde;i risustajalt teehoiukulude katteks h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner of a road and the owner of a protection zone may demand compensation to cover road management costs from persons who damage or pollute the road or the road protection zone. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Veoste v&otilde;i s&otilde;itjate veoga tegelev ettev&otilde;tja peab andma tee omanikule tema n&otilde;udmisel andmeid teed kasutavate s&otilde;idukite, vedude mahu, teekonna ning s&otilde;itude sageduse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An undertaking engaged in the carriage of cargo or passengers shall provide the owner of a road, if the owner so requires, with information on vehicles using the road, the volume of transport operations, routes used and the frequency of journeys. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tee ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi kasutamise ning kaitsmise n&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The requirements for the use and protection of roads and road protection zones shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Veoste ja s&otilde;itjate vedu </eesti>
<inglise>Carriage of cargo and passengers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklust korraldatakse liiklusseaduse (RT I 2001, 3, 6) ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Traffic shall be organised pursuant to the Traffic Act (RT I 2001, 3, 6) and legislation issued on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liiklusv&auml;liseks otstarbeks v&otilde;ib teed kasutada &uuml;ksnes tee omaniku kirjalikul loal ja tema kehtestatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A road may be used for non-traffic purposes only with the written permission of the owner and under the conditions established by the owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui avalikult kasutatav tee suletakse liiklusv&auml;lise &uuml;rituse korraldamiseks, on asjaomase loa saanud isik kohustatud liikluse &uuml;mberkorraldamisega seotud kulud tee omanikule h&uuml;vitama. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a public road is closed for the organisation of a non-traffic event, the person who was granted appropriate permission is required to compensate the owner of the road for costs related to the re-arrangement of traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Nii koormaga kui ka koormata liikleva s&otilde;iduki suurimad lubatud m&otilde;&otilde;tmed ning massi ja teljekoormused kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The maximum permissible measurements, weight and axle load of laden and unladen vehicles shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) S&otilde;itjate turvalisuse tagamiseks peab tee omanik hoolitsema nii tee kui ka s&otilde;itjate peale- ja mahamineku kohtade ohutuse eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In order to ensure the safety of passengers, the owner of a road shall ensure the safety of the road and of the locations designated for the taking up and setting down of passengers. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Lasteveo- v&otilde;i muu &uuml;hiss&otilde;iduliini avamiseks on vaja tee omaniku kirjalikku n&otilde;usolekut. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Written permission from the owner of a road is necessary to open a route for the carriage of children or another public transport route. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Laste ja teiste reisijate ohutuse tagamiseks v&otilde;ib tee omanik seada nii ajutisi kui ka alalisi piiranguid muude s&otilde;idukite liiklemiseks &uuml;hiss&otilde;idukite marsruudil. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) In order to ensure the safety of children and other passengers, the owner of a road may establish temporary or permanent restrictions on other vehicle traffic on a public transport route. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Erateed ja reaalservituudiga erateed ning tasulist teed peab tee omanik lubama tasuta kasutada alarms&otilde;idukil ja erakorralise v&otilde;i s&otilde;jaseisukorra ajal kaitsev&auml;e s&otilde;idukil. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The owner of a private road, a private road encumbered with real servitude or a toll road shall permit emergency vehicles and, during a state of emergency or a state of war, vehicles of the armed forces to use the road without charge. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudel s&otilde;idukitel peab tee omanik lubama teed tasuta kasutada ainult juhul, kui avalikult kasutatav tee on avarii v&otilde;i loodus&otilde;nnetuse tagaj&auml;rgede likvideerimiseks suletud. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner of a road is required to permit other vehicles to use the road without charge only if a public road is closed for the elimination of the effects of an accident or natural disaster. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Liiklusv&auml;line teabevahend </eesti>
<inglise>Non-traffic means of information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Liiklusv&auml;line teabevahend on reklaamiseaduses (RT I 1997, 52, 835; 1999, 27, 388; 30, 415; 2001, 23, 127) nimetatud kuulutus, teadaanne v&otilde;i m&auml;rgis, mis ei ole ette n&auml;htud liikluse korraldamiseks v&otilde;i mis ei ole liikluskorraldusvahendi kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uete kohane. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A non-traffic means of information is an announcement, notice or sign specified in the Advertising Act (RT I 1997, 52, 835; 1999, 27, 388; 30, 415; 2001, 23, 127) which is not prescribed for the organisation of traffic or which does not conform to the requirements established concerning traffic control devices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi paigaldamise loa annab maa omanik tee omaniku kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul ja tema seatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Permission for the installation of a non-traffic means of information shall be granted by the owner of the land with the written permission of the owner of the road and under the conditions established by the owner of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>Teele ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi alale v&otilde;ib paigaldada liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi, mis: </eesti>
<inglise>Non-traffic means of information may be installed on a road and in a road protection zone if such means of information: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ei eksita liiklejat ega varja tema eest liikluskorraldusvahendit; </eesti>
<inglise>1) do not mislead road users or obstruct their view of traffic control devices; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei raskenda liikluskorraldusvahendi eristamist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) do not make it difficult to distinguish a traffic control device; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei ohusta liiklust liikleja pimestamisega ega t&auml;helepanu hajutamisega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) do not pose a traffic hazard by dazzling road users or distracting their attention; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ei piira n&auml;htavust ristmikul. </eesti>
<inglise>4) do not restrict visibility at junctions. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud n&otilde;uete eiramisega tekitatud kahju peab liiklejale h&uuml;vitama teabevahendi paigaldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused by disregard of such requirements shall be compensated to road users by the person who installed the means of information. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kiirteele ning rahvusvahelisele maanteele ja nende kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi alale v&otilde;ib liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi paigaldada ainult r&ouml;&ouml;pselt tee teljega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Non-traffic means of information may be installed on motorways and international roads and in protection zones of such motorways and roads only if the means of information are parallel to the centre line of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajutise liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi v&otilde;ib l&uuml;hiajalise &uuml;rituse v&otilde;i s&uuml;ndmuse ajaks paigaldada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary non-traffic means of information may be installed for the duration of a short-term event under the conditions specified in subsection (4) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maanteele ja maantee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi alale v&otilde;ib liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi paigaldada k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud tingimusel, kui teabevahendi s&otilde;iduteepoolse serva kaugus s&otilde;idutee &auml;&auml;rest on v&auml;hemalt 12 meetrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Non-traffic means of information may be installed on roads and in road protection zones under the conditions provided for in subsection (2) of this section if the distance between the edge of the means of information closest to the carriageway and the edge of the carriageway is at least twelve metres. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ljapoole tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndit v&otilde;ib liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi paigaldada maa omaniku loal. </eesti>
<inglise>Non-traffic means of information may be installed outside a road protection zone with the permission of the owner of the land. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teele v&otilde;i tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndisse tee omaniku n&otilde;usolekuta paigaldatud liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi peab paigaldaja tee omaniku n&otilde;udel viivitamata k&otilde;rvaldama. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Non-traffic means of information which are installed on roads or in road protection zones without the consent of the owner of the road shall be immediately removed by the person who installed the means of information if the owner of the road so demands. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ude t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral on tee omanikul &otilde;igus teabevahend k&otilde;rvaldada. </eesti>
<inglise>If this requirement is not met, the owner of the road has the right to remove the means of information. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabevahendi k&otilde;rvaldamise kulud kannab teabevahendi paigaldaja. </eesti>
<inglise>The costs of removing the means of information shall be borne by the person who installed such means of information. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Erakorraline vedu ja s&otilde;it </eesti>
<inglise>Extraordinary carriage and journey </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Erakorralised on vedu ja s&otilde;it, mil suurem&otilde;&otilde;tmelise v&otilde;i raskekaalulise veose v&otilde;i veoseta s&otilde;iduki kas v&otilde;i &uuml;ks suurim m&otilde;&otilde;de, mass v&otilde;i teljekoormus &uuml;letab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;ike 4 alusel kehtestatud suuruse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Carriage or a journey is extraordinary if one of the maximum measurements or the maximum weight or axle load of a vehicle laden with a large or heavy load or of an unladen vehicle exceeds the figures established on the basis of subsection 33 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avalikult kasutataval teel on erakorraline vedu ja s&otilde;it lubatud eriloaga ja eritasu eest ning &uuml;ksnes loal m&auml;rgitud marsruudil ja tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Extraordinary carriage or an extraordinary journey is permitted on public roads by a special permit and for an additional fee and only according to the itinerary and under the conditions specified in the permit. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee omanikule erakorralise veo v&otilde;i s&otilde;iduga tekitatud kulutuste h&uuml;vitamise ja eritasu m&auml;&auml;rad ning erilubade v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The rates of compensation for costs incurred by owners of roads for extraordinary carriage or extraordinary journeys, the size of the additional fees and the procedure for the issue of special permits shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevus teel ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis </eesti>
<inglise>Activities on roads and in road protection zones </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teel ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis on tee omaniku n&otilde;usolekuta keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are prohibited on roads and in road protection zones without the consent of the owner of the road: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ehitada n&auml;htavust piiravaid hooneid v&otilde;i rajatisi ning rajada istandikku; </eesti>
<inglise>1) construction of buildings or constructions which restrict visibility, or establishment of plantations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ehitada kiirendus- v&otilde;i aeglustusrada, peale- v&otilde;i mahas&otilde;iduteed, alalist v&otilde;i ajutist m&uuml;&uuml;gipunkti v&otilde;i muud teeninduskohta; </eesti>
<inglise>2) construction of acceleration lanes, deceleration lanes, entry slip roads, exit slip roads, permanent or temporary sales facilities and other service facilities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) takistada jalak&auml;ijate liiklemist neid h&auml;iriva tegevusega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) obstruction of pedestrian traffic by activities which disturb pedestrians; </inglise>
<eesti>4) paigaldada valgustusseadet v&otilde;i teabe- ja reklaamivahendit; </eesti>
<inglise>4) installation of lighting installations, means of information and means of advertising; </inglise>
<eesti>5) korraldada spordiv&otilde;istlust v&otilde;i muud rahva&uuml;ritust; </eesti>
<inglise>5) organisation of sports events and other public events; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kaevandada maavara ja maa-ainest; </eesti>
<inglise>6) extraction of earth deposits or earth substances; </inglise>
<eesti>7) teha metsa uuendamiseks lageraiet; </eesti>
<inglise>7) performance of clear cutting for reforestation purposes; </inglise>
<eesti>8) teha veere&zcaron;iimi muutust p&otilde;hjustavat maaparandus- v&otilde;i muud teehoiuv&auml;list t&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>8) performance of land improvement operations or other work not connected with road management which alters the water regime. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi maa omanik on kohustatud kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis hoidma korras teemaaga k&uuml;lgneva kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi maa-ala ja sellel paikneva rajatise ning k&otilde;rvaldama v&otilde;i lubama k&otilde;rvaldada n&auml;htavust piirava istandiku, puu, p&otilde;&otilde;sa v&otilde;i muu liiklusele ohtliku rajatise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner of the land in a road protection zone is required to maintain the area of the protection zone adjacent to the road area and structures located therein and to remove or permit removal of plantations, trees and bushes which restrict visibility and other constructions which pose a traffic hazard. </inglise>
<eesti>Ta peab v&otilde;imaldama paigaldada teega k&uuml;lgnevale kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi kinnistule talihooldeks ajutisi lumet&otilde;kkeid, rajada lumevalle ja kraave tuisklume t&otilde;kestamiseks ning paisata lund v&auml;ljapoole teemaad, kui nimetatud tegevus ei takista juurdep&auml;&auml;su tema elukohale ja varale. </eesti>
<inglise>The owner of the land shall allow installation of temporary snow fences for winter maintenance and construction of snow-walls and ditches to combat blowing snow on the registered immovable in the protection zone adjacent to the road area, and allow snow to be removed to outside the road area if such activity does not obstruct access to the residence or property of the owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mitmele omanikule kuuluvate teede ristumiskohal vastutab iga omanik ohutuks liiklemiseks vajaliku tee seisundi eest talle kuuluva kinnisasja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At junctions of roads in the ownership of several owners, each owner is responsible for maintaining the road in the necessary state for safe traffic within the scope of the immovable belonging to the owner. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Uue tee ristumiskoha ehitamise kulud kannab omanik, kes n&otilde;uab teede &uuml;hendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Costs incurred from the construction of a new junction with a road shall be borne by the owner who demands that the roads be joined. </inglise>
<eesti>Teede omanike kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib kulud jaotada. </eesti>
<inglise>Costs may be divided by agreement of the owners of the roads. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Kohustused, j&auml;relvalve ja vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations, Supervision and Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee omaniku &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and obligations of owner of road </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee omanik on kohustatud j&auml;lgima tee seisundit ja hoidma tee korras, k&otilde;rvaldama teelt liiklust ohustava v&otilde;i n&auml;htavust piirava istandiku, puu, p&otilde;&otilde;sa v&otilde;i muu liiklusele ohtliku rajatise ning korraldama tee kasutamist ja kaitset. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The owner of a road is required to monitor the state of the road and to maintain the road, to remove plantations, trees and bushes which restrict visibility and other constructions which pose a traffic hazard from the road and to organise the use and protection of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui pinnase sulamise, vihma v&otilde;i muude liiklust oluliselt m&otilde;jutavate tegurite t&otilde;ttu on tee konstruktsioon n&otilde;rgenenud ja liiklus v&otilde;ib teed kahjustada v&otilde;i liigelda on ohtlik, v&otilde;ib tee omanik tee v&otilde;i selle osa teatavaks ajaks sulgeda v&otilde;i teel liiklust piirata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The owner of a road may close the road or a part thereof for a certain period of time or restrict traffic on the road if the load-bearing part of the road has deteriorated due to soil thawing, rain or other factors significantly affecting traffic and if traffic may damage the road, or if traffic on the road is dangerous. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee sulgemisest v&otilde;i liikluspiirangutest tuleb teatada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 31 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Notification shall be given of closure of the road or traffic restrictions on the road pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection 31 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tee omanikul on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda eratee kasutajalt tee kasutamisega seotud kulude katteks h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The owner of a private road has the right to demand compensation from users of the private road to cover costs related to the use of the road. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tee&auml;&auml;rse metsa kaitsemetsale vastavad kasutamise viisid v&otilde;ib metsaseadusele (RT I 1998, 113/114, 1872; 1999, 54, 583; 82, 750; 95, 843; 2000, 51, 319; 102, 670) vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rata metsaomanik. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The owner of a forest adjacent to a road may determine the ways of use of the forest, which are appropriate for a protection forest, pursuant to the Forest Act (RT I 1998, 113/114, 1872; 1999, 54, 583; 82, 750; 95, 843; 2000, 51, 319; 102, 670). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tee&auml;&auml;rne mets m&auml;&auml;ratakse tee omaniku taotlusel v&otilde;i &uuml;ldistes huvides planeeringuga kaitsemetsaks, kui see on vajalik: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A forest adjacent to a road shall be designated as a protection forest by a plan on the application of the owner of the road or in the public interest if this is necessary to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tee kahjuliku m&otilde;ju k&uuml;lgnevale kinnisasjale v&otilde;i keskkonnale v&auml;ltimiseks v&otilde;i v&auml;hendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) prevent or decrease the harmful effects of the road on the adjacent immovable or the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tee kaitsmiseks kahjulike loodusm&otilde;jude eest v&otilde;i liiklusohutuse huvides. </eesti>
<inglise>2) protect the road from the harmful effects of nature or in the interest of traffic safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tee omanik on kohustatud liiklejale h&uuml;vitama tee kasutamisk&otilde;lbmatuse t&otilde;ttu ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusakti rikkumise t&otilde;ttu tekitatud kahju, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The owner of a road is required to compensate road users for damage caused due to the road being unusable or due to the violation of this Act or legislation issued on the basis thereof, except in the cases specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi maa omaniku &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and obligations of owner of land in road protection zone </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi maa omanik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda tee omanikult piirangute v&otilde;i servituutide t&otilde;ttu tekkinud kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The owner of the land in a road protection zone may demand compensation from the owner of the road for damage incurred due to restrictions or servitude. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui teede ristumiskoha n&auml;htavuse parandamiseks ei ole hoonet v&otilde;i muud ehitist tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis v&otilde;imalik ega otstarbekas lammutada, tuleb s&otilde;iduohutuse huvides paigaldada liikluskorraldusvahend v&otilde;i muu t&otilde;ke. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If it is neither possible nor practical to demolish a building or other structure located in a road protection zone in order to improve visibility at a road junction, a traffic control device or other barrier shall be installed in the interests of traffic safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud ohutusn&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist kontrollivad Politseiamet ja Maanteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Compliance with the safety requirements specified in subsection (2) of this section shall be monitored by the Police Board and the Road Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse t&auml;itmise j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision of compliance with law </inglise>
<eesti>(1) J&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uetest kinnipidamise &uuml;le korraldavad Maanteeamet ja Politseiamet ning tee omanik k&auml;esolevas seaduses loetletud &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi j&auml;rgides. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervision of compliance with the requirements of this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof shall be organised by the Road Administration, the Police Board and the owner of the road in adherence to the rights and obligations set out in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse ja selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktide n&otilde;uete rikkumiste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks on &otilde;igus koostada ettekirjutusi politseiametnikul ning teede- ja sideministri volitatud ametnikul k&otilde;igi teede puhul ning kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu volitatud ametnikul tema omavalitsuse omandis olevate teede puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Police officers and officials authorised by the Minister of Transport and Communications have the right to prepare precepts for the elimination of violations of this Act and legislation issued on the basis thereof with regard to all roads, and authorised officials of local government councils have the right to prepare such precepts with regard to roads in the ownership of the corresponding local governments. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku vastutus teekasutus- ja teekaitsen&otilde;uete rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of legal person for violation of road use requirements and road protection requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui juriidiline isik tee omaniku loata: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If, without the permission of the owner of the road, a legal person: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kasutab teed spordi- ja teisteks rahva&uuml;ritusteks ning muudeks liiklusv&auml;listeks kogunemisteks - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) uses the road for a sports event or other public event or for other non-traffic assemblies, a fine of 10 000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kasutab liiklemiseks normidele mittevastavate m&otilde;&otilde;tmete, massi v&otilde;i teljekoormusega v&otilde;i teed muul viisil kahjustavat s&otilde;idukit - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>2) uses a vehicle for traffic on the road and the measurements, mass or axle load of the vehicle do not conform to the rules, or uses a vehicle which damages the road in any other manner, a fine of 10 000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>(18.04.2001 j&otilde;ust. 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.04.2001 entered into force 17.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 241) </inglise>
<eesti>3) teeb teel teehoiuv&auml;list t&ouml;&ouml;d, paigutab teele t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi v&otilde;i ehitus- v&otilde;i metsamaterjali, ehitab hoone v&otilde;i rajatise v&otilde;i rajab istandiku - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>3) performs work not connected with road management on the road, places work equipment, building material or timber on the road, constructs a building or construction or establishes a plantation, a fine of 10 000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaevandab tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis maavara, teeb metsa lageraiet v&otilde;i muud looduskeskkonda &uuml;mberkujundavat t&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i ehitab tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndisse hoone, rajatise v&otilde;i muu objekti v&otilde;i rajab istandiku - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>4) extracts earth deposits, cuts clear forest or performs other work altering the natural environment in a road protection zone, or constructs a building, construction or other object or establishes a plantation in a road protection zone, a fine of 10 000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>5) paigaldab liiklusv&auml;lise teabevahendi - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 50 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>5) installs a non-traffic means of information, a fine of 10 000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui juriidiline isik: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a legal person: </inglise>
<eesti>1) j&auml;tab t&auml;itmata tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi ja sellel asuva rajatise korrashoiu n&otilde;uded v&otilde;i kahjustab v&otilde;i risustab teed ja tee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndit v&otilde;i ei k&otilde;rvalda liikluskorraldusvahendit etten&auml;htud ajaks - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 10 000 kuni 30 000 krooni; </eesti>
<inglise>1) fails to comply with the maintenance requirements of a road protection zone or a construction located therein, or damages or pollutes a road or a road protection zone, or fails to remove a traffic control device by the prescribed deadline, a fine of 10 000 to 30 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) rikub tee kohta kehtestatud liiklusohutusn&otilde;udeid, j&auml;tab etten&auml;htud ajaks rakendamata abin&otilde;ud teataval teel&otilde;igul liikluse keelamiseks v&otilde;i piiramiseks, j&auml;tab liiklusohtliku koha korrastamata v&otilde;i liiklust ohustava v&otilde;i n&auml;htavust piirava takistuse, puu, p&otilde;&otilde;sa v&otilde;i istandiku k&otilde;rvaldamata, j&auml;tab n&otilde;utud liikluskorraldus- v&otilde;i teet&auml;histusvahendi paigaldamata v&otilde;i paigaldab selle n&otilde;uetevastaselt - m&auml;&auml;ratakse talle rahatrahv 30 000 kuni 50 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>2) violates traffic safety requirements established concerning a road, fails to apply measures to prohibit or restrict traffic on a certain section of a road by the prescribed deadline, fails to maintain a location which is dangerous to traffic, fails to remove an impediment, tree, bush or plantation which poses a traffic hazard or restricts visibility, fails to install a required traffic control device or road marking device, or installs the device against the requirements, a fine of 30 000 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed on the legal person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juriidilise isiku karistamine ei v&auml;lista &otilde;iguserikkumise toimepannud f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku karistamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Punishment of a legal person does not preclude the punishment of a natural person who has committed an offence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juriidilise isiku haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja arutab ja m&auml;&auml;rab talle karistuse halduskohtunik. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Administrative court judges shall hear and impose punishments on legal persons for matters concerning administrative offences committed by legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramise ja vaidlustamise ning j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsuse t&auml;itmise ja muid k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 loetletud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asju menetletakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 351; 54, 346; 54, 348; 54, 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544; 86, 548; 95, 609; 89, 578; 95, 613; 2001, 18, 87; 21, 115; 116; 31, 174; 42, 236) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustiku (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Matters of imposition of and appeal against punishments, enforcement of court judgments which have entered into force and other matters concerning administrative offences specified in subsections (1) or (2) of this section are heard pursuant to the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 351; 54, 346; 54, 348; 54, 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544; 86, 548; 95, 609; 89, 578; 95, 613; 2001, 18, 87; 21, 115; 116; 31, 174; 42, 236) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238). </inglise>
